cs.PF, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.PL

The paper discusses a tool for performance modeling of loop kernels, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.PF (Performance), followed by cs.AR (Architecture), as the tool requires knowledge of the underlying hardware. The paper also touches upon software engineering (cs.SE) and parallel computing (cs.DC), as it deals with multicore processors and scaling behavior. Finally, the tool is implemented as a program (cs.PL), which is another possible sub-category.
